    "longBusinessSummary": "Quy NHON Port Joint STOCK Company operates a port in the gulf of Quy Nhon. It handles cargoes, including bulk container, over length, and overweight cargoes. The company is also involved in the cargo handling and warehousing services; tug board services; cargo transportation by waterway; agency for transportation; supplying facilities for port operation; food and ship chandler services; oil business; mechanical product processing; repairing machine, equipment, and means of transportation on land and by waterway; wharf repairing; assembly of berth equipment; and civil and industrial construction activities. Its port helps connecting maritime routes to international ports, such as Manila, Singapore, Taiwan, Thailand, Japan, and Russia. The company was incorporated in 2009 and is based in Quy Nhon, Vietnam. Quy NHON Port Joint STOCK Company is a subsidiary of Vietnam Maritime Corporation - Joint Stock Company.",
